==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pelvis
<hw>Pel"vis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a basin, laver;
cf. Gr. <?/, <?/, bowl.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The
pelvic arch, or the pelvic arch together with the sacrum. See
<cref>Pelvic arch</cref>, under <er>Pelvic</er>, and
<er>Sacrum</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The calyx of a crinoid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pelvis of the kidney</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>,
<cd>the basinlike cavity into which the ureter expands as it joins the
kidney.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>pelycosaur</ent>⟦br⟧
